Linked List is a data structure used for storing a collection of elements.<br>
Each item has a pointer to the next/previous item. Such Lists are called singly linked lists.
If each item has a pointer to both previous and the next item, it is a Doubly linked list.
This post has implemented a few mehtods on a linked list to help you visualise how it looks.
Use the buttons to add/seach/delete nodes.
